AGI - "Shut up, little man". Pay a small part of the cost. And there's nothing that can replace Starlink." Thus Elon Musk>, on X, responded to the post of the Polish Foreign Minister Radoslaw Sikorski, > according to which it is Warsaw to pay the Starlink services for Ukraine. "Apart from the ethics of threatening the victim of an attack, if SpaceX proves to be an unreliable supplier we will be forced to look for other suppliers," Sikorski wrote.&nbsp;
Musk is back to ask that you immediately arrive at peace in Ukraine, ammoning that without its satellite system &nbsp; Kiev's defense would collapse immediately. "I literally challenged Putin to a body-to-body combat for Ukraine," he wrote on X. "My Starlink system is the backbone of the Ukrainian army. All their first line would collapse if I shut it down."
Musk expressed his disgust for "years of massacre in a <a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2025-03-08/musk-starlink-ucraina-30336968/">&nbsp; stale situation that Ukraine&nbsp;</a> will inevitably lose". He added: "Whoever really cares about the matter, really think and really understand, wants the meat grinder to stop. Peace now." &nbsp;
<h2>Musk, Starlink will never turn off its terminals
Starlink will never turn off its terminals in Ukraine. "To be extremely clear, no matter how much I disagree with Ukrainian politics, Starlink will never turn off its terminals," writes the billionaire, "without Starlink, the Ukrainian lines would collapse, because the Russians can block all the other communications! We would never do such a thing, nor would we use it as a commodity of exchange." &nbsp;
<h2> Information against oligarchs
Also on X, Musk called "sanctions to the first 10 Ukrainian oligarchs, especially to those who own villas in Monaco". According to the patron of Tesla,&nbsp;<a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2025-03-07/musk-proposte-conflitto-ucraina-30333453/"> if restrictive measures were imposed This is the key to the puzzle."
<h2>Starlink and its impact</h2>
Starlink, Musk's satellite system, was fundamental to ensure communications in Ukraine during the conflict. Its ability to provide internet in remote areas and in emergency situations makes it a crucial resource. However, Musk underlined its power to unilaterally decide to &nbsp;<a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2025-03-06/starlink-crisi-globali-30329861/">spegnere il servizio</a>, raising questions on the private control of such strategic infrastructures.
<h2>Zelensky: "We work to have means of defence and peace"</h2>
Volodymyr&nbsp;Zelensky returned to call for peace>, justice and security guarantees for his country. "This week, Russia has made hundreds of attacks against our people with various types of weapons: about 1,200 air bombs, almost 870 drones and more than 80 missiles of various kinds," he wrote on Telegram. "Every air bomb used by Russia contains components provided to evade sanctions. This weapon contains over 82,000 foreign components," he recalled.
"We work with our partners to ensure that decisions that help save lives are made: the provision of air defense, investments in our defense production, strengthening sanctions against Russia," he said. "And we continue our work to achieve just peace and provide reliable security guarantees," he assured.
